Aing lieur is a traditional Korean game that is played with a set of five stones The stones are placed in a circle and each player takes turns throwing the stones into the circle The goal of the game is to be the first player to get all five stones into the circle The game is usually played with two players but can also be played with more The game is a great way to practice hand-eye coordination and strategy

A lock is a mechanism used to control access to a shared resource A shared lock is a type of lock that allows multiple users to access the same resource at the same time It is typically used in situations where multiple users need to access the same data or resource such as a shared file or database Shared locks are usually implemented using a locking protocol such as the twophase locking protocol which ensures that all users have exclusive access to the resource while it is being used
